They're recovering in isolation in hospital and are set to be discharged within a week. JOHANNESBURG – A new video footage has been released of the 12 boys who were rescued from a cave in Thailand. They're recovering in isolation in hospital and are set to be discharged within a week. Some of the boys can be seen sitting up in their beds. For the time being, their parents are only able to see them through protective glass. Following Tuesday’s miraculous rescue, the focus has now shifted to the recovery of the boys. WATCH: Finally free: Boys & coach rescued from Thai cave 